From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
Subject: [ldn_mitm] Integrate switch-lan-play relay bridge via IPC channel

Wire ldn_mitm into the switch-lan-play relay so that "wireless local" games
work over the internet.  Communication with the relay server is entirely UDP.

IPC protocol
------------
Each ldn_mitm outbound datagram sent to 127.0.0.1:LDN_IPC_PORT (11453) has
the format:
  [4 bytes: IPv4 destination address, network byte order]
  [N bytes: LDN protocol packet (LANPacketHeader + payload)]

The destination can be 10.13.255.255 (broadcast, for Scan) or 10.13.x.y
(unicast, for ScanResp and other directed replies).  This makes the FULL
Scan ↔ ScanResp discovery exchange work across the relay.

Key changes
-----------
1. lanplay_bridge.{hpp,cpp}  (new files)
   Reads sdmc:/tmp/lanplay.status (written by switch-lan-play every ~2 s).
   Exposes: lanplay_is_active(), lanplay_get_virtual_ip(),
            lanplay_get_broadcast(), lanplay_get_ipc_sockaddr()

2. LDUdpSocket  (lan_discovery.hpp / lan_discovery.cpp)
   - getBroadcast() returns 10.13.255.255 when active
   - sendBroadcast() overrides send both normal LAN broadcast AND IPC unicast
     to 127.0.0.1:LDN_IPC_PORT (broadcast always goes to relay)

3. getFakeMac() / getNodeInfo()
   Use virtual IP (10.13.x.y) so advertised IPs route through the relay.

4. initialize()
   Skips nifmSetLocalNetworkMode(true) when switch-lan-play is active to
   keep the internet connection alive for the relay UDP socket.

Apply with: patch -p1 -d ldn_mitm < patches/0001-lanplay-bridge.patch

